2019 is off to a great start for Afrobeat sensation Burna Boy and “Surrender” crooner Mr. Eazi as they have been announced to perform at Coachella in Los Angeles, California. The annual music festival would host hundreds of thousands of fans from around the world to an experience of diverse sound and energetic performances from top artists like Ariana Grande, Childish Gambino, Solange, Diplo and many more. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-825589 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM.jpeg" alt="" width="1000" height="1251" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM.jpeg 863w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM-478x598.jpeg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM-445x557.jpeg 445w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM-192x240.jpeg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM-384x480.jpeg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WhatsApp-Image-2019-01-03-at-8.16.13-AM-479x600.jpeg 479w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> The complete line up was announced on Wednesday night, January 2nd 2019 and as usual Coachella will be staged on consecutive three-day weekends in April, with identical lineups each weekend, from the weekend of Friday, April 12 & 19, 13 & 20, 14 & 21, 2019. Mr Eazi will perform on the second week while Burna Boy is set to perform the following weekend. Read More: Burna Boy Lashes Out At Coachella Listing In time past, Top Nigerian artistes like King Sunny Ade and Wizkid have both been listed to perform at the glamorous event in 2017 and 2018 respectively, although Wizkid was unable to make it due to unavoidable circumstances. Last year Beyoncé shook the crowd with her performance and now it is time for Oluwa Burna and ‘your boy’ Eazi to take centre stage and put on a great show.